Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and
dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve and peel @shallot{1}. Grate
one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}; place in a #large bowl{}.
Mince remaining shallot. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%oz}.

> Cut broccoli florets into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes; roast 15-20 minutes.

Meanwhile, to bowl with grated shallot, add @ground beef{10%oz}, garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup},
half the parsley, salt, and pepper. Gently combine, then form into two 1-inch-tall
loaves. Place on one side of a second baking sheet.

Brush tops of meatloaves with half the @ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Bake on middle rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary.

Once meatloaves have baked 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss green
beans on empty side with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

Return to middle rack until green beans are tender and meatloaves are cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{½%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add minced
shallot; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Sprinkle with @flour{1%tbsp}; whisk vigorously to combine. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}
and @water{½%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened and saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in remaining parsley; season with salt and pepper.

Slice meatloaves crosswise.

Divide meatloaves, potato wedges, and green beans between plates. Spoon gravy over
meatloaves and serve.